Using the property \(Y_2 = X_1 + X_2 - Y_1\), \(Z\) is rewritten as \(Z = Y_1 + X_1 + X_2\). By linearity of expectation:
\[
E(Z) = E(Y_1) + E(X_1) + E(X_2).
\]
- \(E(X_1) = \theta = 2\) and \(E(X_2) = \theta = 2\).
