* RESPONSE 1 *
**************
The solution calculates \(P(A_1 \cup A_2 \cup A_3)\) using the inclusion-exclusion principle (Theorem 1.1-6). The given probabilities are substituted into the formula:

\[
P(A_1 \cup A_2 \cup A_3) = P(A_1) + P(A_2) + P(A_3) - P(A_1 \cap A_2) - P(A_1 \cap A_3) - P(A_2 \cap A_3) + P(A_1 \cap A_2 \cap A_3)
\]

\[
= \frac{1}{3} + \frac{1}{3} + \frac{1}{3} - \frac{1}{9} - \frac{1}{9} - \frac{1}{9} + \frac{1}{27}
\]

After computation, the exact probability is \(\frac{19}{27}\). This is approximated as a decimal: \(\frac{19}{27} \approx 0.7037037\). Rounded to three decimal places (since the fourth decimal digit is 7, which is greater than or equal to 5), the result is 0.704.

The solution summarizes the final answer as 0.704. The unit is probability, which is unitless, so no unit is specified.

